I"´<p><label for="cbic2019-toc.jpg" class="margin-toggle">âŠ•</label><input type="checkbox" id="cbic2019-toc.jpg" class="margin-toggle" /><span class="marginnote"><img class="fullwidth" src="/assets/img/cbic2019-toc.jpg" /><br />Artificial Signal Transduction across Membranes.</span> A key conundrum in the construction of an artificial cell is to simultaneously maintain a robust physical barrier to the external environment, while also providing efficient exchange of information across this barrier. Biomimicry provides a number of avenues by which such requirements might be met. Herein, we provide a brief introduction to the challenges facing this field and explore progress to date.</p>
